    "predict_settings": {
      "isPredictLevel": false
    },
    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. **Run and Discuss:** Look at the paint_diagonal(color) function:\r\n   - How does the first `if` statement control whether the Painter paints and moves? \r\n   - What does each ***nested*** `if` inside it do?\r\n2. **Add Code:** Finish the code inside the `paint_diagonal(color)` function defintion:\r\n   - Add a \"parent\" `if` statement to check if the Painter `has_paint()`. \r\n   - Inside this \"parent\" `if` statment, add an `if` to check if the Painter is facing south, and if so: \r\n      - Paint using the parameter `color`.\r\n      - Check if the Painter can move, and if so, move.\r\n      - Turn left.\r\n      - Check again if the Painter can  move, and if so, move.\r\n3. **Run and Test:** Run your program and check if the Painter paints a diagonal line from the top left to the bottom right of the Neighborhood. <br>\r\n4. **Discuss:** Why isn't the Painter painting a diagonal line?\r\n\t- **Hint:** What does calling `paint_diagonal(color)` once do? What would happen if you called it repeatedly?\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# Create Painter object\nsofia = Painter()\n\n# Function to move while painter can move\ndef move_while_can():\n  while sofia.can_move():\n    sofia.move()\n\n# Function to take all the paint\ndef take_all_paint():\n  while sofia.is_on_bucket():\n    sofia.take_paint()\n\n# Function to turn right\ndef turn_right():\n  sofia.turn_left()\n  sofia.turn_left()\n  sofia.turn_left()\n\n# Function to paint a diagonal line\ndef paint_diagonal(color):\n  if sofia.has_paint():\n    if sofia.is_facing_east():\n      sofia.paint(color)\n      if sofia.can_move():\n        sofia.move()\n      turn_right()\n      if sofia.can_move():\n        sofia.move()\n  # ADD SECOND SET OF IF AND NESTED IF STATEMENTS HERE\n\n\ntake_all_paint()\n# ADD paint_diagonal FUNCTION CALL HERE\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
